		<hr size="1">Yep I should have mentioned that, I picked the zones I did specifically because there are often large numbers of people in them.  If I got tired of soloing I could easily do an LFG and get a pick up group immediately, in fact I often had to go /role just to keep people from asking me to join them when I wanted to solo..<img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle>  Grouping is very important at all levels, you need to practice working in a group environment, things that work great for you solo can get an entire group wiped out fast and things that work great in groups can in turn get you wasted if you try them solo or with too few people in the group.  </P><P>I suggest trying a wide variety of groups as well, all caster, all melee, balanced, etc.  You will fit into ANY group, it's just a matter of chosing the right song line up.  The new spell sets are great for quickyl swapping, I have a few saved, Chant, Swarm, Caster Group, Melee Group and Raid.</P><P>Just hit 59 today, yay, but the treants that were just giving me 8% per 9 kills are not giving me 1% every 2 kills... so I either chant 200 treants at 2.5 minutes each... or I find a new place to hunt.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
