		<hr size="1">If you are using your DS, you do not want to use the snare song until just prior to 20% (when they run) health.  The slower they are attacking, the less damage your DS is doing.  Needlites are perfect for skill ups in defense - low damage but real fast attacks.</P><P><BR>As for the MA...don't worry much about it.  You won't be doing it long.  Even when I was in my 20's I started having trouble being MA.  I could do it, but I sure was mana sponging off the cleric.</P><P>MA's don't deal with adds anyway...it's not their job.  Someone else should be doing it.  You can't truly do your job as MA if you have to stop attacking one to get an add.</P><P>As for dealing with an enchanter and you missing the mez msgs...that's something only you can really do.  Ask the chanter to hit the msg more than once is a good option, but make sure that the /g color is very vivid.  Mine's a very bright light blue - it sticks out when my spell stuff is dark dark blue.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
