		<hr size="1">I don't think I've ever used the AOE slow song...the use is so limited that it's not worth the gem slot, IMO.</P><P>Why have misses on?  They really don't matter.  If you have multiple mobs on you missing it's not that big of a deal.  Hits, on the other hand, are important.</P><P>I have my hits on, misses off, MOB hits on, misses off and everyone elses hits/misses off (why do I care how much damage they are doing? if I need to know what mob they are hitting, I have assist for that)</P><P>Helps that I run at whatever resolution is higher than 1024x768 (I thinki 1240x1024 or something like that).  I also made the font smaller so I can shrink the boxes a bit (horizontally) allowing me to put more boxes along the bottom.</P><P>Lastly, since you can't turn off non-melee damage from all and leave only yours on (sucks big time), I made another window and stuck it up in the top left and minimized it (at least made it completely invisible with just text showing) so I can check it if need be but it won't spam my important boxes.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
